1.  Extract $P$ and $X$ using `take()` and `unwrap()`.
2.  Extract the subtrees $B$ and $C$ from $X$.
3.  Re-link $P.right$ to $B$ and $G.left$ to $C$.
4.  Re-link $X.left$ to $P$ and $X.right$ to $G$.
5.  Use assertions to help Verus verify the subset relationships of the views, ensuring the BST property is easily proven by the SMT solver.

